The paper discusses the use of machine learning methods for neuroimaging data analysis, which falls under the intersection of computer science and neuroscience. The paper specifically focuses on the use of the scikit-learn library, which is a popular machine learning library in Python. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as they are also relevant to the analysis of neuroimaging data. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are less likely but still possible sub-categories as they can also be applied to the analysis of natural language processing tasks in neuroimaging research.
